 with that.</td><td>I will need help with this.</td></tr><tr><td>Come</td><td>He comes to work early.</td><td>He came to work early.</td><td>He will come to work early.</td></tr><tr><td>Read</td><td>I read a book.</td><td>I read a book last week.</td><td>I will read a book next week.</td></tr><tr><td>Live</td><td>They live in New York.</td><td>They lived in New York.</td><td>They will live in New York.</td></tr><tr><td>Pay</td><td>She pays the bills.</td><td>She paid the bills.</td><td>She will pay the bills.</td></tr><tr><td>Could</td><td>I could help with that.</td><td>I could have helped with that.</td><td>I could help with that.</td></tr><tr><td>Know</td><td>He knows the answer.</td><td>He knew the answer.</td><td>He will know the answer.</td></tr><tr><td>Spend</td><td>We spend time together.</td><td>We spent time together.</td><td>We will spend time together.</td></tr><tr><td>Serve</td><td>The restaurant serves breakfast.</td><td>The restaurant served breakfast.</td><td>The restaurant will serve breakfast.</td></tr><tr><td>Ask</td><td>I ask questions in class.</td><td>I asked questions in class.</td><td>I will ask questions in class.</td></tr><tr><td>Expect</td><td>She expects good results.</td><td>She expected good results.</td><td>She will expect good results.</td></tr><tr><td>See</td><td>I see the problem now.</td><td>I saw the problem yesterday.</td><td>I will see the problem later.</td></tr><tr><td>Understand</td><td>They understand the issue.</td><td>They understood the issue.</td><td>They will understand the issue.</td></tr><tr><td>Take</td><td>I take notes during lectures.</td><td>I took notes during lectures.</td><td>I will take notes during lectures.</td></tr><tr><td>Remember</td><td>I remember the date.</td><td>I remembered the date.</td><td>I will remember the date.</td></tr><tr><td>Call</td><td>She calls her friend.</td><td>She called her friend.</td><td>She will call her friend.</td></tr><tr><td>Mean</td><td>What does this mean?</td><td>What did t