He affirmed his commitment.</td><td>He will affirm his commitment.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->','List of verbs that starts with A','','inherit','closed','closed','','18-revision-v1','','','2024-07-26 21:44:54','2024-07-26 21:44:54','',18,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=19',0,'revision','',0),(20,1,'2024-07-26 21:53:18','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2024-07-26 21:53:18','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=20',0,'post','',0),(21,1,'2024-07-26 21:54:37','2024-07-26 21:54:37','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verb: Amplify</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Meaning:</strong> To make something larger, louder, or more powerful; to increase the size, extent, or effect of something. In a broader sense, it can also mean to elaborate on a statement by providing more details.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Synonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Increase</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Intensify</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Boost</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enhance</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Magnify</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Antonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Decrease</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Diminish</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Lessen</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Reduce</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Minimize</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Usage in Different Contexts:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Scientific Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Amplify</strong> is often used in the context of increasing sound or signal strength. For example: \"The scientists used a device to amplify the weak signal.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Music Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In music, <strong>amplify</strong> refers to making sounds louder, typically through electronic means. For example: \"The guitarist used an amplifier to amplify the sound of the guitar.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Communication Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Amplify</strong> can describe elaborating on a point or argument to make it clearer or more persuasive. For example: \"She amplified her argument with additional statistics and examples.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Social Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In social settings, <strong>amplify</strong> might describe making a message more widespread or impactful. For example: \"Social media can amplify voices that were previously unheard.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Examples of Common Mistakes:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"They amplified their voices by shouting.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"They amplified their voices using a microphone.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"The teacher amplified the lesson by speaking slower.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"The teacher amplified the lesson by providing more examples.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Collocations:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Amplify sound</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Amplify effects</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Amplify message</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Amplify signal</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Amplify voice</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Present Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>amplify</strong> my voice with a microphone.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>amplify</strong> the message by sharing it on social media.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>amplifies</strong> the sound with his guitar amplifier.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>amplifies</strong> her argument with data.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>amplify</strong> the music at the concert.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>amplify</strong> their influence through partnerships.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Past Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>amplified</strong> my voice at the meeting yesterday.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>amplified</strong> the message with your presentation last week.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>amplified</strong> the signal using advanced technology.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>amplified</strong> her concerns in the report.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>amplified</strong> the effects of the campaign by targeting a larger audience.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>amplified</strong> their reach by collaborating with influencers.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Future Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>will amplify</strong> my efforts to ensure success.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>will amplify</strong> your message through effective communication.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>will amplify</strong> the volume for the event tomorrow.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>will amplify</strong> her points in the upcoming debate.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>will amplify</strong> our strategy to reach more customers.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>will amplify</strong> their initiatives for better results.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Frequency:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>often</strong> amplify my ideas during discussions.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>rarely</strong> amplify your voice when speaking in public.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>always</strong> amplifies his points with examples.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>usually</strong> amplifies her presentations with visuals.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>frequently</strong> amplify our campaigns with targeted ads.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>sometimes</strong> amplify their projects to reach a wider audience.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Place:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I amplify my voice <strong>here</strong> for better clarity.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You amplify the message <strong>there</strong> to reach more people.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He amplifies the sound <strong>in the auditorium</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She amplifies her influence <strong>in the community</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We amplify our efforts <strong>at the headquarters</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They amplify their presence <strong>across the region</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Time:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I amplify my efforts <strong>now</strong> for immediate results.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You amplify the message <strong>later</strong> during the meeting.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He amplifies the music <strong>during</strong> the event.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She amplifies her points <strong>when</strong> she presents her findings.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We amplify our strategies <strong>as soon as</strong> we get feedback.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They amplify their initiatives <strong>before</strong> launching them.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Manner:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I amplify my voice <strong>clearly</strong> for everyone to hear.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You amplify the message <strong>effectively</strong> using various channels.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He amplifies the sound <strong>powerfully</strong> with his equipment.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She amplifies her argument <strong>convincingly</strong> with statistics.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We amplify our campaign <strong>strategically</strong> for maximum impact.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They amplify their efforts <strong>deliberately</strong> to ensure success.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Quantity:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I amplify my efforts <strong>significantly</strong> for better results.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You amplify your message <strong>to a large extent</strong> by using media.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He amplifies the sound <strong>considerably</strong> with the new speakers.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She amplifies her points <strong>a lot</strong> to make them clearer.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We amplify our resources <strong>greatly</strong> to improve efficiency.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They amplify their initiatives <strong>extensively</strong> for broader impact.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Affirmation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>definitely</strong> amplify my arguments to make them stronger.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>surely</strong> amplify your message for wider reach.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>certainly</strong> amplifies the music for the concert.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>truly</strong> amplifies her efforts to succeed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>undoubtedly</strong> amplify our campaigns to attract attention.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>absolutely</strong> amplify their presence to stand out.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Negation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>never</strong> amplify rumors or misinformation.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>barely</strong> amplify your voice in small gatherings.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>doesn\'t</strong> usually amplify trivial matters.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>rarely</strong> amplifies her voice unless necessary.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>hardly</strong> amplify minor issues in meetings.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>don\'t</strong> amplify gossip or unverified news.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Doubt:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>might</strong> amplify my efforts if needed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>could</strong> amplify your message for more impact.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>may</strong> amplify the sound if required.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>might</strong> amplify her points for clarity.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>possibly</strong> amplify our strategies depending on the situation.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>might</strong> amplify their initiatives if the opportunity arises.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Amplify (Verb) - A','','publish','open','open','','amplify-verb-a','','','2024-07-26 23:01:34','2024-07-26 23:01:34','',0,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=21',0,'post','',0),(22,1,'2024-07-26 21:54:37','2024-07-26 21:54:37','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verb: Amplify</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Meaning:</strong> To increase the volume or intensity of something, often used in the context of sound or signal strength. It can also mean to expand or elaborate on something, such as a statement or idea.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>List of phrases with the verb \"Amplify\"</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Present:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I amplify the sound to make it louder.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You amplify the message for better clarity.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He amplifies his voice during the presentation.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She amplifies the radio to hear the news.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We amplify the signals to improve reception.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They amplify the speaker’s voice at the concert.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Past:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I amplified the sound during the last meeting.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You amplified the message yesterday.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He amplified his voice in the speech.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She amplified the radio earlier today.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We amplified the signals last week.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They amplified the speaker’s voice last night.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Future:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I will amplify the sound for the performance.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You will amplify the message next time.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He will amplify his voice in the next speech.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She will amplify the radio during the event.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We will amplify the signals to enhance the system.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They will amplify the speaker’s voice in the future.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Amplify (Verb) - A','','inherit','closed','closed','','21-revision-v1','','','2024-07-26 21:54:37','2024-07-26 21:54:37','',21,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=22',0,'revision','',0),(23,1,'2024-07-26 21:56:39','2024-07-26 21:56:39','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verb: Abandon</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Meaning:</strong> To leave something or someone behind, typically in a way that is considered neglectful, or to cease to support or look after something or someone. It can also mean to give up on a plan, idea, or project.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Synonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Desert</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Forsake</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Relinquish</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Leave</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Quit</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Antonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Continue</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Retain</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Maintain</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Preserve</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Keep</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Usage in Different Contexts:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Professional Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Abandon</strong> might be used in project management. For example: \"We decided to abandon the project due to unforeseen challenges and financial constraints.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Social Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In social interactions, <strong>abandon</strong> can describe someone\'s behavior. For example: \"He felt hurt when his friends decided to abandon him during the crisis.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Legal Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Abandon</strong> could be relevant in legal discussions about property or custody. For example: \"The court decided that the parent had abandoned their custody rights.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Literary Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In literature, <strong>abandon</strong> might illustrate a character’s actions or decisions. For example: \"The character abandoned their former life to pursue a new, unknown adventure.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Examples of Common Mistakes:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"She abandoned the idea and then continued with it.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"She abandoned the idea and decided to pursue a different one.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"He will abandon his car if it breaks down soon.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"He will abandon his plans for the trip if the car breaks down.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Collocations:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Abandon a plan</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Abandon a project</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Abandon ship</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Abandon an idea</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Abandon someone</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Present Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandon my old plans for new opportunities.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandon the project when it becomes unfeasible.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandons his old car in the garage.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandons her initial thoughts after further consideration.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandon the idea due to its complexity.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandon the ship in an emergency.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Past Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandoned my old plans last year.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandoned the project after the issues were discovered.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandoned his car last month.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandoned her initial thoughts after the meeting.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandoned the idea earlier this year.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandoned the ship during the storm.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Future Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I will abandon my old plans if a better option arises.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You will abandon the project if it becomes too risky.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He will abandon his car if it breaks down again.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She will abandon her initial thoughts after receiving feedback.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We will abandon the idea if it proves impractical.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They will abandon the ship if necessary.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Frequency:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>sometimes</strong> abandon plans when they no longer serve me.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>often</strong> abandon projects that lack potential.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>rarely</strong> abandons tasks once he starts them.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>usually</strong> abandons ideas that don\'t align with her goals.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>frequently</strong> abandon outdated processes for efficiency.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>occasionally</strong> abandon old strategies for better results.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Place:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandon my bag <strong>here</strong> whenever I visit.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandon the documents <strong>there</strong> for review.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandons his car <strong>outside</strong> the building.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandons her coat <strong>inside</strong> the room.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandon the materials <strong>nearby</strong> for convenience.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandon the supplies <strong>everywhere</strong> in the office.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Time:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandon projects <strong>early</strong> to focus on priorities.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandon meetings <strong>sometimes</strong> due to scheduling conflicts.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandons plans <strong>immediately</strong> when they don\'t work.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandons her work <strong>late</strong> at night if needed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandon outdated practices <strong>eventually</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandon strategies <strong>soon</strong> after evaluating them.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Manner:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandon tasks <strong>carefully</strong> to avoid mistakes.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandon ideas <strong>hastily</strong> when pressured.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandons goals <strong>reluctantly</strong> if necessary.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandons projects <strong>deliberately</strong> for better ones.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandon methods <strong>easily</strong> when ineffective.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandon plans <strong>quickly</strong> if challenges arise.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Quantity:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandon <strong>all</strong> attempts to convince him.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandon <strong>many</strong> tasks due to limited time.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandons <strong>some</strong> projects for more important ones.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandons <strong>several</strong> plans after reconsideration.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandon <strong>a few</strong> ideas each year.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandon <strong>countless</strong> strategies that fail.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Affirmation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>definitely</strong> abandon unproductive routines.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>certainly</strong> abandon unprofitable ventures.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>surely</strong> abandons unworkable solutions.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>truly</strong> abandons incompatible partnerships.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>undoubtedly</strong> abandon failing initiatives.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>clearly</strong> abandon irrelevant goals.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Negation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>never</strong> abandon my principles.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>rarely</strong> abandon your commitments.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>doesn\'t</strong> abandon his responsibilities.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>won\'t</strong> abandon her beliefs easily.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>cannot</strong> abandon our mission.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>hardly</strong> abandon their allies.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Doubt:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>possibly</strong> abandon outdated methods next year.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>might</strong> abandon plans if circumstances change.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>could</strong> abandon ideas if they prove ineffective.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>may</strong> abandon the project if it’s too costly.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>might</strong> abandon our goals if necessary.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>possibly</strong> abandon the partnership if it fails.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Abandon (Verb) - A','','publish','open','open','','abandon-verb-a','','','2024-07-26 22:58:13','2024-07-26 22:58:13','',0,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=23',0,'post','',0),(24,1,'2024-07-26 21:56:39','2024-07-26 21:56:39','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verb: Abandon</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Meaning:</strong> To leave something or someone behind, typically in a way that is considered neglectful or to cease to support or look after something or someone. It can also mean to give up on a plan, idea, or project.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>List of phrases with the verb \"Abandon\"</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Present:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandon my old plans for new opportunities.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandon the project when it becomes unfeasible.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandons his old car in the garage.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandons her initial thoughts after further consideration.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandon the idea due to its complexity.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandon the ship in an emergency.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Past:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandoned my old plans last year.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandoned the project after the issues were discovered.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandoned his car last month.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandoned her initial thoughts after the meeting.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandoned the idea earlier this year.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandoned the ship during the storm.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Future:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I will abandon my old plans if a better option arises.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You will abandon the project if it becomes too risky.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He will abandon his car if it breaks down again.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She will abandon her initial thoughts after receiving feedback.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We will abandon the idea if it proves impractical.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They will abandon the ship if necessary.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Abandon (Verb) - A','','inherit','closed','closed','','23-revision-v1','','','2024-07-26 21:56:39','2024-07-26 21:56:39','',23,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=24',0,'revision','',0),(25,1,'2024-07-26 21:57:57','2024-07-26 21:57:57','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verb: Abase</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Meaning:</strong> To behave in a way that belittles or degrades someone; to lower someone in rank, prestige, or esteem. It often implies a reduction in dignity or self-respect.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Synonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Humiliate</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Degrade</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Demean</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Belittle</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Lower</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Antonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Elevate</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Honor</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Exalt</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Respect</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Praise</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Usage in Different Contexts:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Professional Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Abase</strong> might be used in discussions about workplace dynamics or leadership styles. For example: \"A good leader does not abase their team members but uplifts them.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Social Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In social settings, <strong>abase</strong> can describe interactions that harm someone\'s self-esteem. For example: \"She refused to abase herself by responding to the taunts.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Psychological Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Abase</strong> could be relevant in discussions about self-esteem and personal growth. For example: \"Constant criticism can cause individuals to abase themselves in their own minds.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Historical Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In history, <strong>abase</strong> might illustrate how certain groups were treated. For example: \"The conquerors sought to abase the local population to establish control.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Examples of Common Mistakes:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><st