"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Frequency:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>sometimes</strong> abandon plans when they no longer serve me.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>often</strong> abandon projects that lack potential.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>rarely</strong> abandons tasks once he starts them.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>usually</strong> abandons ideas that don\'t align with her goals.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>frequently</strong> abandon outdated processes for efficiency.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>occasionally</strong> abandon old strategies for better results.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Place:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandon my bag <strong>here</strong> whenever I visit.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandon the documents <strong>there</strong> for review.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandons his car <strong>outside</strong> the building.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandons her coat <strong>inside</strong> the room.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandon the materials <strong>nearby</strong> for convenience.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandon the supplies <strong>everywhere</strong> in the office.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Time:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandon projects <strong>early</strong> to focus on priorities.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandon meetings <strong>sometimes</strong> due to scheduling conflicts.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandons plans <strong>immediately</strong> when they don\'t work.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandons her work <strong>late</strong> at night if needed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandon outdated practices <strong>eventually</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandon strategies <strong>soon</strong> after evaluating them.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Manner:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandon tasks <strong>carefully</strong> to avoid mistakes.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandon ideas <strong>hastily</strong> when pressured.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandons goals <strong>reluctantly</strong> if necessary.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandons projects <strong>deliberately</strong> for better ones.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandon methods <strong>easily</strong> when ineffective.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandon plans <strong>quickly</strong> if challenges arise.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Quantity:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abandon <strong>all</strong> attempts to convince him.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abandon <strong>many</strong> tasks due to limited time.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abandons <strong>some</strong> projects for more important ones.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abandons <strong>several</strong> plans after reconsideration.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abandon <strong>a few</strong> ideas each year.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abandon <strong>countless</strong> strategies that fail.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Affirmation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>definitely</strong> abandon unproductive routines.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>certainly</strong> abandon unprofitable ventures.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>surely</strong> abandons unworkable solutions.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>truly</strong> abandons incompatible partnerships.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>undoubtedly</strong> abandon failing initiatives.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>clearly</strong> abandon irrelevant goals.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Negation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>never</strong> abandon my principles.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>rarely</strong> abandon your commitments.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>doesn\'t</strong> abandon his responsibilities.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>won\'t</strong> abandon her beliefs easily.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>cannot</strong> abandon our mission.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>hardly</strong> abandon their allies.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Doubt:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>possibly</strong> abandon outdated methods next year.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>might</strong> abandon plans if circumstances change.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>could</strong> abandon ideas if they prove ineffective.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>may</strong> abandon the project if it’s too costly.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>might</strong> abandon our goals if necessary.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>possibly</strong> abandon the partnership if it fails.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Abandon (Verb) - A','','inherit','closed','closed','','23-revision-v1','','','2024-07-26 22:58:13','2024-07-26 22:58:13','',23,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=29',0,'revision','',0),(30,1,'2024-07-26 22:59:52','2024-07-26 22:59:52','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verb: Abase</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Meaning:</strong> To behave in a way that belittles or degrades someone; to lower someone in rank, prestige, or esteem. It often implies a reduction in dignity or self-respect.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Synonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Humiliate</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Degrade</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Demean</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Belittle</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Lower</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Antonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Elevate</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Honor</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Exalt</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Respect</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Praise</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Usage in Different Contexts:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Professional Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Abase</strong> might be used in discussions about workplace dynamics or leadership styles. For example: \"A good leader does not abase their team members but uplifts them.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Social Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In social settings, <strong>abase</strong> can describe interactions that harm someone\'s self-esteem. For example: \"She refused to abase herself by responding to the taunts.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Psychological Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Abase</strong> could be relevant in discussions about self-esteem and personal growth. For example: \"Constant criticism can cause individuals to abase themselves in their own minds.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Historical Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In history, <strong>abase</strong> might illustrate how certain groups were treated. For example: \"The conquerors sought to abase the local population to establish control.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Examples of Common Mistakes:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"He will abase his confidence to get the job.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"He will abase himself to please his superiors, though it\'s not advisable.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"They abase themselves over the mistake and then corrected it.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"They felt abased by the mistake but then corrected it.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Collocations:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Abase oneself</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Abase someone</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Abase one’s dignity</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Feel abased</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Refuse to abase</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Present Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abase myself by accepting unfair treatment.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abase yourself when you agree to their unreasonable demands.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abases himself to gain approval from others.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abases herself by not standing up for her rights.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abase ourselves by not valuing our contributions.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abase themselves when they conform to peer pressure.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Past Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abased myself by accepting an unfair offer.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abased yourself during the meeting yesterday.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abased himself in front of the crowd last week.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abased herself to please others in her previous job.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abased ourselves by compromising our values.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abased themselves by giving in to the opposition.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Future Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I will not abase myself for anyone\'s approval.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You will abase yourself if you let them take advantage of you.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He will abase himself to avoid conflict, although he shouldn’t.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She will abase herself if she continues to doubt her worth.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We will not abase ourselves, as we value our integrity.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They will abase themselves if they prioritize others\' opinions over their own.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Frequency:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>never</strong> abase myself for others’ opinions.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>rarely</strong> abase yourself in confrontations.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>often</strong> abases himself to seek validation.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>sometimes</strong> abases herself when feeling insecure.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>usually</strong> do not abase ourselves in negotiations.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>frequently</strong> abase themselves in competitive environments.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Place:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abase myself <strong>here</strong> to keep the peace.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abase yourself <strong>there</strong> to fit in.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abases himself <strong>in public</strong> when criticized.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abases herself <strong>at work</strong> to avoid conflict.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abase ourselves <strong>among friends</strong> to maintain harmony.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abase themselves <strong>at school</strong> due to peer pressure.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Time:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abase myself <strong>occasionally</strong> when pressured.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abase yourself <strong>sometimes</strong> during arguments.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abases himself <strong>when necessary</strong> to avoid trouble.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abases herself <strong>frequently</strong> in tense situations.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abase ourselves <strong>only</strong> in emergencies.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abase themselves <strong>often</strong> to gain favor.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Manner:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abase myself <strong>reluctantly</strong> when required.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abase yourself <strong>unwillingly</strong> in certain situations.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abases himself <strong>subtly</strong> to avoid attention.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abases herself <strong>gracefully</strong> when she apologizes.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abase ourselves <strong>quickly</strong> if needed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abase themselves <strong>openly</strong> to show remorse.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Quantity:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I abase myself <strong>very</strong> little these days.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You abase yourself <strong>too</strong> much for others\' comfort.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He abases himself <strong>a lot</strong> to gain approval.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She abases herself <strong>barely</strong> in challenging situations.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We abase ourselves <strong>as</strong> little <strong>as</strong> possible.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They abase themselves <strong>significantly</strong> to win trust.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Affirmation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>certainly</strong> refuse to abase myself for anyone.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>truly</strong> abase yourself too often.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>definitely</strong> abases himself in stressful situations.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>undoubtedly</strong> abases herself to avoid conflict.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>surely</strong> abase ourselves when it seems necessary.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>certainly</strong> abase themselves for acceptance.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Negation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>never</strong> abase myself without a reason.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>hardly</strong> ever abase yourself in front of others.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>doesn\'t</strong> usually abase himself unless pressured.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>won\'t</strong> abase herself just to fit in.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>cannot</strong> abase ourselves without losing respect.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>rarely</strong> abase themselves in their community.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Doubt:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>might</strong> abase myself if there\'s no other option.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>could</strong> abase yourself under pressure.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>may</strong> abase himself if things get tough.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>might</strong> abase herself to please others.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>possibly</strong> abase ourselves if we see no alternatives.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>might</strong> abase themselves in challenging circumstances.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Abase (Verb) - A','','inherit','closed','closed','','25-revision-v1','','','2024-07-26 22:59:52','2024-07-26 22:59:52','',25,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=30',0,'revision','',0),(31,1,'2024-07-26 23:01:34','2024-07-26 23:01:34','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verb: Amplify</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Meaning:</strong> To make something larger, louder, or more powerful; to increase the size, extent, or effect of something. In a broader sense, it can also mean to elaborate on a statement by providing more details.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Synonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Increase</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Intensify</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Boost</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enhance</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Magnify</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Antonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Decrease</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Diminish</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Lessen</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Reduce</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Minimize</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Usage in Different Contexts:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Scientific Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Amplify</strong> is often used in the context of increasing sound or signal strength. For example: \"The scientists used a device to amplify the weak signal.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Music Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In music, <strong>amplify</strong> refers to making sounds louder, typically through electronic means. For example: \"The guitarist used an amplifier to amplify the sound of the guitar.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Communication Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Amplify</strong> can describe elaborating on a point or argument to make it clearer or more persuasive. For example: \"She amplified her argument with additional statistics and examples.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Social Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In social settings, <strong>amplify</strong> might describe making a message more widespread or impactful. For example: \"Social media can amplify voices that were previously unheard.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Examples of Common Mistakes:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"They amplified their voices by shouting.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"They amplified their voices using a microphone.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"The teacher amplified the lesson by speaking slower.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"The teacher amplified the lesson by providing more examples.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Collocations:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Amplify sound</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Amplify effects</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Amplify message</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Amplify signal</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Amplify voice</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Present Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>amplify</strong> my voice with a microphone.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>amplify</strong> the message by sharing it on social media.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>amplifies</strong> the sound with his guitar amplifier.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>amplifies</strong> her argument with data.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>amplify</strong> the music at the concert.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>amplify</strong> their influence through partnerships.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-