ng\">Usage with Adverbs of Frequency:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>often</strong> amplify my ideas during discussions.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>rarely</strong> amplify your voice when speaking in public.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>always</strong> amplifies his points with examples.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>usually</strong> amplifies her presentations with visuals.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>frequently</strong> amplify our campaigns with targeted ads.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>sometimes</strong> amplify their projects to reach a wider audience.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Place:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I amplify my voice <strong>here</strong> for better clarity.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You amplify the message <strong>there</strong> to reach more people.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He amplifies the sound <strong>in the auditorium</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She amplifies her influence <strong>in the community</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We amplify our efforts <strong>at the headquarters</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They amplify their presence <strong>across the region</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Time:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I amplify my efforts <strong>now</strong> for immediate results.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You amplify the message <strong>later</strong> during the meeting.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He amplifies the music <strong>during</strong> the event.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She amplifies her points <strong>when</strong> she presents her findings.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We amplify our strategies <strong>as soon as</strong> we get feedback.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They amplify their initiatives <strong>before</strong> launching them.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Manner:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I amplify my voice <strong>clearly</strong> for everyone to hear.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You amplify the message <strong>effectively</strong> using various channels.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He amplifies the sound <strong>powerfully</strong> with his equipment.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She amplifies her argument <strong>convincingly</strong> with statistics.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We amplify our campaign <strong>strategically</strong> for maximum impact.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They amplify their efforts <strong>deliberately</strong> to ensure success.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Quantity:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I amplify my efforts <strong>significantly</strong> for better results.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You amplify your message <strong>to a large extent</strong> by using media.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He amplifies the sound <strong>considerably</strong> with the new speakers.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She amplifies her points <strong>a lot</strong> to make them clearer.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We amplify our resources <strong>greatly</strong> to improve efficiency.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They amplify their initiatives <strong>extensively</strong> for broader impact.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Affirmation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>definitely</strong> amplify my arguments to make them stronger.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>surely</strong> amplify your message for wider reach.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>certainly</strong> amplifies the music for the concert.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>truly</strong> amplifies her efforts to succeed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>undoubtedly</strong> amplify our campaigns to attract attention.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>absolutely</strong> amplify their presence to stand out.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Negation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>never</strong> amplify rumors or misinformation.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>barely</strong> amplify your voice in small gatherings.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>doesn\'t</strong> usually amplify trivial matters.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>rarely</strong> amplifies her voice unless necessary.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>hardly</strong> amplify minor issues in meetings.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>don\'t</strong> amplify gossip or unverified news.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Doubt:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>might</strong> amplify my efforts if needed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>could</strong> amplify your message for more impact.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>may</strong> amplify the sound if required.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>might</strong> amplify her points for clarity.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>possibly</strong> amplify our strategies depending on the situation.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>might</strong> amplify their initiatives if the opportunity arises.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Amplify (Verb) - A','','inherit','closed','closed','','21-revision-v1','','','2024-07-26 23:01:34','2024-07-26 23:01:34','',21,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=31',0,'revision','',0),(32,1,'2024-07-26 23:04:48','2024-07-26 23:04:48','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verb: Add</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Meaning:</strong> To combine or join something with something else, resulting in an increase or enhancement; often used in arithmetic, cooking, and general contexts where items are combined to form a larger whole.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Synonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Combine</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Include</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Attach</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Append</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Supplement</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Antonyms:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Subtract</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Remove</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Deduct</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Eliminate</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Decrease</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Usage in Different Contexts:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Mathematical Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Add</strong> is commonly used in mathematics to refer to combining numbers. For example: \"When you add 5 and 3, you get 8.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Cooking Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In cooking, <strong>add</strong> means incorporating ingredients into a dish. For example: \"Add the sugar to the mixture and stir well.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Digital Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In digital contexts, <strong>add</strong> can refer to incorporating files or data into a system. For example: \"Add the file to your presentation.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Social Context:</strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Socially, <strong>add</strong> might refer to including someone in a group or activity. For example: \"Let\'s add John to our team.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Examples of Common Mistakes:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"Add two to the list and subtract it.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"Add two to the list.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"I add the salt after the dish is cooked.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"Add the salt before the dish is cooked.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Collocations:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Add value</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Add up</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Add together</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Add ingredients</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Add fuel to the fire</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Present Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>add</strong> sugar to my coffee every morning.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>add</strong> your name to the guest list.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>adds</strong> more tasks to his schedule.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>adds</strong> a touch of color to her paintings.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>add</strong> new members to the club regularly.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>add</strong> details to their project report.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Past Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>added</strong> extra cheese to the pizza yesterday.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>added</strong> your signature to the document.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>added</strong> more books to his collection last month.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>added</strong> a note to the memo.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>added</strong> new features to the software last week.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>added</strong> a few more people to the team.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\