 the students to the museum.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Examples of Common Mistakes:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"I will bring my book to the school.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"I will bring my book to school.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Incorrect Usage:</strong> \"She brings me a lot of happiness.\"<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Correction:</strong> \"She brings me much happiness.\"</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Collocations:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bring about</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bring back</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bring down</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bring in</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bring up</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bring together</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Present Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>bring</strong> my lunch to work every day.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>bring</strong> joy to everyone around you.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>brings</strong> his own tools for the job.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>brings</strong> her children to school in the morning.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>bring</strong> fresh ideas to every meeting.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>bring</strong> their dog to the park regularly.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Past Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>brought</strong> the report to the meeting yesterday.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>brought</strong> your friend to the party last week.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>brought</strong> an umbrella in case it rained.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>brought</strong> the issue to our attention last month.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>brought</strong> our concerns to the management earlier.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>brought</strong> the new product to market last year.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Future Tense Phrases:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>will bring</strong> the materials to the workshop tomorrow.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>will bring</strong> your expertise to the project next week.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>will bring</strong> his laptop to the presentation.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>will bring</strong> the documents when she visits us.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>will bring</strong> our findings to the conference.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>will bring</strong> the changes to the team shortly.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Frequency:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>always bring</strong> a notebook to meetings.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>often bring</strong> snacks for everyone.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>rarely brings</strong> his work home.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>usually brings</strong> a gift for special occasions.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>sometimes bring</strong> additional resources to the project.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>frequently bring</strong> up new ideas in discussions.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Place:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I will bring the package <strong>to the office</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You should bring the documents <strong>to the meeting room</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He brought his tools <strong>to the workshop</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She brings her car <strong>to the garage</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We will bring the supplies <strong>to the site</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They bring their children <strong>to the playground</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Time:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I bring the files <strong>every morning</strong> to work.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You bring your reports <strong>daily</strong> to the manager.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He brought the presentation <strong>last week</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She will bring the results <strong>tomorrow</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We bring new updates <strong>regularly</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They will bring the equipment <strong>by Friday</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Manner:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I bring my ideas <strong>enthusiastically</strong> to the team.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You bring your expertise <strong>efficiently</strong> to every project.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He brought the news <strong>calmly</strong> to his colleagues.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She brings her children <strong>carefully</strong> to school.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We bring our solutions <strong>creatively</strong> to the table.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They bring their guests <strong>warmly</strong> into their home.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Quantity:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I bring <strong>a lot</strong> of experience to the team.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You bring <strong>several</strong> suggestions for improvement.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He brought <strong>many</strong> examples to illustrate his point.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She will bring <strong>a few</strong> new ideas to the meeting.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We bring <strong>plenty</strong> of enthusiasm to our work.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They bring <strong>some</strong> additional resources to the project.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Affirmation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>definitely bring</strong> my best effort to every task.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>certainly bring</strong> a positive attitude to the team.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>undoubtedly brings</strong> valuable insights to the discussion.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>surely brings</strong> expertise to the project.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>absolutely bring</strong> our full commitment.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>positively bring</strong> results to the table.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Negation:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>do not bring</strong> unnecessary items to the office.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>never bring</strong> your work home.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>does not bring</strong> personal issues to meetings.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>is not bringing</strong> any new ideas today.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>do not bring</strong> distractions to the project.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>are not bringing</strong> the changes this week.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Usage with Adverbs of Doubt:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I <strong>might bring</strong> the report if needed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>You <strong>could bring</strong> additional data if you have it.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>He <strong>may bring</strong> his notes to the session.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>She <strong>might not bring</strong> the document without confirmation.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>We <strong>could bring</strong> more resources if required.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>They <strong>may not bring</strong> their usual equipment.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Bring (Common usage Verb) - B','','inherit','closed','closed','','49-revision-v1','','','2024-07-26 19:56:54','2024-07-26 19:56:54','',49,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=50',0,'revision','',0),(51,1,'2024-07-26 20:03:16','2024-07-26 20:03:16','<!-- wp:template-part {\"slug\":\"top-bar\",\"theme\":\"dualtone\",\"className\":\"site-topbar\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:template-part {\"slug\":\"footer\",\"theme\":\"dualtone\",\"className\":\"site-footer\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"metadata\":{\"name\":\"sidebar-content-wrap\"},\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:columns {\"metadata\":{\"name\":\"sidebar-content-columns\"},\"align\":\"wide\",\"className\":\"is-style-sidebar-content\",\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"blockGap\":{\"top\":\"0px\",\"left\":\"0px\"}}}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns alignwide is-style-sidebar-content\"><!-- wp:column {\"width\":\"\",\"metadata\":{\"name\":\"content\"},\"className\":\"is-style-content-right\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-style-content-right\"><!-- wp:template-part {\"slug\":\"site-title\",\"theme\":\"dualtone\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:template-part {\"slug\":\"default-loop\",\"theme\":\"dualtone\"} /--></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column {\"width\":\"\",\"metadata\":{\"name\":\"sidebar\"},\"className\":\"is-style-sidebar-left\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-style-sidebar-left\"><!-- wp:group {\"metadata\":{\"name\":\"sticky container\"},\"style\":{\"position\":{\"type\":\"sticky\",\"top\":\"0px\"}}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:template-part {\"slug\":\"sidebar-header\",\"theme\":\"dualtone\",\"tagName\":\"header\",\"className\":\"site-header\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:template-part {\"slug\":\"sidebar-content\",\"theme\":\"dualtone\"} /--></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->','Index','Used as a fallback template for all pages when a more specific template is not defined.','publish','closed','closed','','index','','','2024-07-26 20:03:16','2024-07-26 20:03:16','',0,'http://granjacob.com/blog/index.php/2024/07/26/index/',0,'wp_template','',0),(52,1,'2024-07-26 20:03:16','2024-07-26 20:03:16','<!-- wp:group {\"tagName\":\"aside\",\"metadata\":{\"name\":\"header-wrap\"},\"style\":{\"position\":{\"type\":\"\"}},\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<aside class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"flex\",\"flexWrap\":\"wrap\",\"justifyContent\":\"center\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:site-logo {\"width\":60,\"shouldSyncIcon\":false} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:site-title {\"level\":0,\"fontSize\":\"large\"} /--></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:categories /-->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"metadata\":{\"name\":\"navigation-wrap\"},\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"padding\":{\"top\":\"var:preset|spacing|050\"}}},\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\" style=\"padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--050)\"><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></aside>\n<!-- /wp:group -->','Sidebar header','','publish','closed','closed','','sidebar-header','','','2024-07-26 20:03:17','2024-07-26 20:03:17','',0,'http://granjacob.com/blog/index.php/2024/07/26/sidebar-header/',0,'wp_template_part','',0),(53,1,'2024-07-26 20:03:17','2024-07-26 20:03:17','<!-- wp:group {\"tagName\":\"aside\",\"metadata\":{\"name\":\"header-wrap\"},\"style\":{\"position\":{\"type\":\"\"}},\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<aside class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"flex\",\"flexWrap\":\"wrap\",\"justifyContent\":\"center\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:site-logo {\"width\":60,\"shouldSyncIcon\":false} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:site-title {\"level\":0,\"fontSize\":\"large\"} /--></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:categories /-->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"metadata\":{\"name\":\"navigation-wrap\"},\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"padding\":{\"top\":\"var:preset|spacing|050\"}}},\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\" style=\"padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--050)\"><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></aside>\n<!-- /wp:group -->','Sidebar header','','inherit','closed','closed','','52-revision-v1','','','2024-07-26 20:03:17','2024-07-26 20:03:17','',52,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=53',0,'revision','',0),(54,1,'2024-07-27 00:28:00','2024-07-27 00:28:00','{\"version\": 3, \"isGlobalStylesUserThemeJSON\": true }','Custom Styles','','publish','closed','closed','','wp-global-styles-listorify','','','2024-07-27 00:28:00','2024-07-27 00:28:00','',0,'http://granjacob.com/blog/index.php/2024/07/27/wp-global-styles-listorify/',0,'wp_global_styles','',0),(55,1,'2024-07-28 06:53:12','2024-07-28 06:53:12','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>...or something like this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://granjacob.com/blog/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','NEPTUNEQL','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2024-07-28 06:53:12','2024-07-28 06:53:12','',2,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=55',0,'revision','',0),(56,1,'2024-07-28 07:21:29','2024-07-28 07:21:29','','Angloblog','','publish','closed','closed','','angloblog','','','2024-07-28 07:21:29','2024-07-28 07:21:29','',0,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?page_id=56',0,'page','',0),(57,1,'2024-07-28 07:21:29','2024-07-28 07:21:29','','Angloblog','','inherit','closed','closed','','56-revision-v1','','','2024-07-28 07:21:29','2024-07-28 07:21:29','',56,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=57',0,'revision','',0),(58,1,'2024-07-28 07:24:16','2024-07-28 07:24:16','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Creating a blog based on categories from an existing WordPress blog involves several steps. The goal is to extract content based on categories and set up a new blog with that content. Here\'s a step-by-step guide to help you achieve this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">1. <strong>Identify the Existing Blog\'s Structure</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before you begin, familiarize yourself with the existing WordPress blog’s categories and content structure. This will help you determine what content you need to extract and how to organize it in the new blog.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">2. <strong>Set Up the New WordPress Blog</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you haven’t already, set up a new WordPress blog. This can be done on a local server (using tools like XAMPP or MAMP) or on a live server with a web host.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Install WordPress</strong>: Follow the <a>WordPress installation guide</a> if you need assistance.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Choose a Theme</strong>: Select a theme that suits your new blog’s purpose and aesthetics.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">3. <strong>Export Content from the Existing Blog</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To extract the content based on categories, you can use the WordPress export tool:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Log in to the Existing WordPress Admin Panel</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Go to Tools > Export</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Select Categories</strong>: Choose the categories you want to export. This will allow you to export only the content associated with those categories.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Download the Export File</strong>: Click on the \"Download Export File\" button to download an XML file containing the selected content.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">4. <strong>Import Content into the New Blog</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now that you have the content exported, you can import it into your new blog:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Log in to the New WordPress Admin Panel</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Go to Tools > Import</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Install WordPress Importer</strong>: If it’s not already installed, you’ll be prompted to install the WordPress Importer plugin.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Run the Importer</strong>: Choose the XML file you exported from the old blog and import it into the new blog.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Assign Authors</strong>: During the import process, you can assign imported content to existing users or create new users.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Check and Adjust Categories</strong>: Ensure that the categories are properly set up in the new blog. You may need to adjust category names, slugs, or parent-child relationships.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">5. <strong>Customize Your New Blog</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After importing the content, you can customize your new blog:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Edit Posts and Pages</strong>: Adjust the content to fit the theme and purpose of the new blog. You might need to update images, links, or media.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Organize Categories</strong>: Ensure that the categories are correctly organized. You can add new categories or merge existing ones as needed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Add Widgets and Plugins</strong>: Enhance your blog with widgets and plugins for added functionality, such as SEO optimization, social sharing, or contact forms.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">6. <strong>Redirect Traffic (If Needed)</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you want to redirect traffic from the old blog to the new one, you can set up redirects:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>301 Redirects</strong>: Use a plugin like <a>Redirection</a> to set up 301 redirects from old URLs to new ones.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Update Internal Links</strong>: Ensure all internal links are updated to point to the new blog’s URLs.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">7. <strong>Test Your New Blog</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before launching, thoroughly test your new blog:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Check Navigation</strong>: Ensure all links work and point to the correct locations.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Test Responsiveness</strong>: Make sure the blog is responsive and works well on different devices.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Verify Content</strong>: Double-check that all content has been correctly imported and formatted.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Additional Tools and Plugins</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Advanced Export Plugins</strong>: For more control over the export process, consider plugins like <a>WP All Export</a> to customize the content export based on categories or other criteria.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Content Migration Services</strong>: If you\'re dealing with a large amount of content or complex requirements, consider using a content migration service or plugin, such as <a href=\"https://cms2cms.com/\">CMS2CMS</a>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Database Access</strong>: For more advanced users, direct access to the database (via phpMyAdmin or a similar tool) can allow for more granular content extraction and manipulation.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Summary</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Creating a new WordPress blog based on categories from an existing blog involves exporting and importing content, setting up categories, and customizing the new site to meet your needs. By following these steps, you can efficiently set up and launch your new blog with content organized by category.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have any specific requirements or run into any issues, feel free to ask for more detailed help!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How can I create a blog based on category of current existing Wordpress blog?','','publish','open','open','','how-can-i-create-a-blog-based-on-category-of-current-existing-wordpress-blog','','','2024-07-28 07:24:16','2024-07-28 07:24:16','',0,'http://granjacob.com/blog/?p=58',0,'post','',0),(59,1,'2024-07-28 07:24:16','2024-07-28 07:24:16','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Creating a blog based on categories from an existing WordPress blog involves several steps. The goal is to extract content based on categories and set up a new blog with that content. Here\'s a step-by-step guide to help you achieve this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">1. <strong>Identify the Existing Blog\'s Structure</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before you begin, familiarize yourself with the existing WordPress blog’s categories and content structure. This will help you determine what content you need to extract and how to organize it in the new blog.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">2. <strong>Set Up the New WordPress Blog</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you haven’t already, set up a new WordPress blog. This can be done on a local server (using tools like XAMPP or MAMP) or on a live server with a web host.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><